{\"ngram\": \"the safety\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 724}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitors\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris Olympics 2024 Shortly after Yee stormed home to clinch gold, TV cameras captured Canada's Mislawchuk being violently sick at the finish line, raising further doubts of pollution levels in the Seine.\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 1003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8824332027636501, \"rank\": 0.12990630602695247, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999965266397, \"rank\": 3.452304464048069e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"Yee\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"TV cameras\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"further doubts\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution levels\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But speaking toTriathlon Magazine Canada, Mislawchuk insisted it was the high temperatures in the final laps of the 10km run that made him so ill after finishing ninth, 52 seconds behind Yee.\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8824332027636501, \"rank\": 0.12990630602695247, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mislawchuk\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"the high temperatures\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1095}, {\"ngram\": \"the final laps\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1113}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10km run\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"Yee\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'For me, whether I was fourth or 55th it does not really matter.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I tried to win a medal and I went out there and was basically in third place with the two French guys for five and a half or 6 km,' Mislawchuk said.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9901818590988184, \"rank\": 0.009543298849824954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"third place\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"five and a half or 6 km\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1392}, {\"ngram\": \"Mislawchuk\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'At my last Olympics there was the injury and with all the stuff that happened there was a lot of \\\"what ifs\\\".\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my last Olympics\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1433}, {\"ngram\": \"the injury\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"all the stuff\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I have no \\\"what ifs\\\" on the day, I went for it, it was absolutely everything.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everything\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I vomited ten times after the race \\u2026 it got hot in the last laps.'\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the last laps\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a separate interview withThe Canadian Press, the 29-year-old brushed off concerns over the water quality in the Seine and said the strong currents and 'scolding' heat were his main issues.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999965266397, \"rank\": 3.452304464048069e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a separate interview\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"Canadian Press\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"the water quality\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"the strong currents\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"' heat\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"his main issues\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The race was strange.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1888, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The race\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was crazy currents which was difficult to deal with and then wet on the bike course from rain in the morning,' he explained.\", \"from\": 1889, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"crazy currents\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike course\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1975}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"the morning\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was then just scolding hot on the run so just all the elements, all the challenges that you can imagine.\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the run\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"so just all the elements\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2084}, {\"ngram\": \"all the challenges\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'But that's triathlon.\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2150, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"triathlon\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Triathlon is in all the venues across the world, different courses, and so I think it comes down to the famous saying, \\\"Adapt or die\\\", and that's what you have to do in this kind of racing.'\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Triathlon\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"all the venues\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2198}, {\"ngram\": \"different courses\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"the famous saying\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2329}, {\"ngram\": \"racing\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mislawchuk added: 'We raced here last year in the test event and I had no issues.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2424, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mislawchuk\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"the test event\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"no issues\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obviously, I am not a doctor, I am not a water specialist, and so, for me, whatever I was reading in the news did not really matter.\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a doctor\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"a water specialist\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2482}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2508}, {\"ngram\": \"the news\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It was like, \\\"I am here to race and that's what my job is\\\".\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 2587, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"my job\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am lucky to call it a job.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2648, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a job\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am here to race and perform.\", \"from\": 2649, \"to\": 2679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Any extra energy wasted thinking about whatever\\u2026 even when the race got cancelled, I told myself, \\\"I have got to use this to my advantage\\\", because I typically train big hours and so I thought maybe it was just an extra day for me to recover, you know.'\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Any extra energy\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2729}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2749}, {\"ngram\": \"my advantage\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2819}, {\"ngram\": \"big hours\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2857}, {\"ngram\": \"just an extra day\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2905}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mislawchuk felt like he was swimming in 'slow motion' due the ferocious currents in the Seine.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3025, \"end\": 3030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999965266397, \"rank\": 3.45